/* Jimmy has to develop a Kids Learning App as his mini-project of Java subject where any State name is 
entered by the user and it displays the name of its capital as per the following list:

Assam : Dispur
Bihar : Patna
Madhya Pradesh : Bhopal
Manipur : Imphal
Mizoram : Aizawl
Sikkim : Gangtok
Uttar Pradesh: Lucknow
Uttarakhand : Dehradun

If any other input is given, then the output must be No Record Found

Help him to implement the logic using switch-case.

Input Format
Reads the name of the state
**Example: **Manipur

Constraints
NA

Output Format
Prints the name of the Capital or No Record Found  */

// code starts from here


import java.util.*;
public class StringSwitchDemo {  
        
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String month= sc.nextLine();
        
        String capital;

        switch (month) {
            case "Assam":
                capital = "Dispur";
                break;
            case "Bihar":
                capital = "Patna";
                break;
            case "Madhya Pradesh":
                capital = "Bhopal";
                break;
            case "Manipur":
                capital = "Imphal";
                break;
            case "Sikkim":
                capital = "Gangtok";
                break;
            case "Uttar Pradesh":
                capital = "Lucknow";
                break;
            case "Uttarakhand":
                capital = "Dehradun";
                break;
            case "Mizoram":
                capital = "Aizawl";
                break;
            default: 
                capital = "No Record Found";
                break;
        }
        System.out.println(capital);
    }
}

